pnpm start         # Production server
pnpm lint          # ESLint on src/
pnpm type-check    # tsc --noEmit
```

**Type generation:**
- **No auto-generated Supabase types.** Types are manually maintained in `packages/shared/src/types.ts` and per-page interfaces.
- The `tsconfig.json` has `"strict": true` — all types must be explicit.

**Environment variables exposed to frontend:**
Only those prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` (from next.config.ts and .env.example):
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY
NEXT_PUBLIC_BUILD_SHA      (injected in next.config.ts)
NEXT_PUBLIC_BUILD_DATE     (injected in next.config.ts)
```

All other env vars (like NAS_EDGE1_API_SECRET) are **server-only** and not accessible from the browser.

---

### 11. **Color & Styling Reference**

From `globals.css`:
```css
--color-background: #ffffff
--color-foreground: #0a0a0a
--color-card: #f8f8f8
--color-primary: #2563eb              /* Blue — action buttons, links */
--color-primary-foreground: #ffffff
--color-success: #16a34a               /* Green — healthy, running */
--color-warning: #d97706               /* Amber — degraded, at-risk */
--color-critical: #dc2626              /* Red — errors, failures */
--color-border: #e4e4e7
--color-muted: #f4f4f5
--color-muted-foreground: #71717a
--radius-lg: 0.75rem
--radius-md: 0.5rem
```

**Usage:**
```tsx
// Success badge
<span className="rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-success/10 text-success">
  Healthy
</span>

// Critical alert box
<div className="rounded-lg border border-critical/30 bg-critical/5 p-4 text-critical">
  Error message
</div>

// Loading skeleton
<div className="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4 animate-pulse h-32" />
```

